@node "Introduction" "Introduction"
@next "Requirements"
@prev "Misc"
TachySearch is an Internet Search Engine, in HTML format, for use with a web
browser. Initially it was intended for use with IBrowse, but it does/should
work with any decent graphical browser that supports tables.

It started as a small project for my personal use. I then shared it with a few
friends who later encouraged me to release it publicly. Well, here it is.

As for the name, it has two sources. First is my Internet Relay Chat nickname
Tachyon, which some people shorten to Tachy. The second source (thank Wouter)
is the medical term "tachy" which means "fast". You could then translate
TachySearch to FastSearch.

TachySearch consists of two basic components. The main search page, and the
hotlist page which is a subset of my own personal WWW hotlist.

Here it is, I'll try to keep it updated and current, I hope you enjoy it.
@endnode

@node "Requirements" "Requirements"
@next "Installation"
@prev "Introduction"
TachySearch's requirements are fairly simple. You will need:

- An HTML 3.x compatible web browser (IE IBrowse, AWeb 2.x, Hyperion,
NetScrape, etc.)

- Datatypes to support JPEG images or a browser that can decode them
internally.

- An Internet connection



Some recommended stuff for more enjoyable web browsing:

- Amiga OS >= 3.0 - A 68020 or greater processor (040+ preferred) - AmiTCP 4.3
or better. This is THE superior TCP/IP stack for the Amiga. The uninformed
have been taken in by fancy GUI interfaces on other TCP/IP stacks, but
extensive testing has proven AmiTCP 4.3 to be the fastest, most resource
efficient, most compatible and most powerful stack available, bar none. -
Graphics board. AGA is old news, ECS is just frusterating. Get a nice fast
graphics board that is CyberGraphX compatible. - CyberGraphX software.
Retargettable graphics here today. - For modem users, grab a new US Robotics
modem. They have consistently been tested faster and more compatible than any
other brand, and models built after August 15th '96 are X2 upgradable. Be
ready when true 56k netsurfing on ordinary phone lines becomes available.
http://x2.usr.com/
@endnode

@node "Installation" "Installation"
@next "Instructions"
@prev "Requirements"
Installation: (for IBrowse users)

Ok, copy the TachySearch directory into the same directory your IBrowse
executable is in. Don't rename any of the files or you get to edit HTML
yourself.

Next load up IBrowse.

Go to the Preferences menu and choose 'General'.

click on Fastlink.

click on ADD.

In the name entry fill in 'Search Engines' or whatever you want the button
labled. (Hmm TachySearch might be a good button label ;')

In the location entry put
'file://localhost/<path:/more/path/>IBrowse/TachySearch/Search.html'

Without the quotes and substitue in your path where you keep IBrowse.

Example:

Name:      Search Engines Location:
file://localhost/WorkI:communications/IBrowse/TachySearch/Search.html

(See the included PrefsWindow.IFF file)

click on OK

Go to the preferences menu item again and choose SAVE SETTINGS.

There should now be a 'Search Engines' fastlink button, click on it and make
sure it loads the search page. If not, sell your computer cause this was so
easy even a monkey could have done it properly the first time. Ok you could
try reading thru this and having another go at it first I guess.

To use it, well, just choose your search engine and type in your search
keywords and hit return.


Good luck,
@endnode

@node "Instructions" "Instructions"
@next "History"
@prev "Installation"
Using Tachysearch is fairly simple. You have three basic choices.

1) You're in a hurry. Just choose the appropriate search engine in the
"QuickSearch's" section at the top of the page, enter the appropriate
keyword(s) and hit return or click search.

2) You have a tough one and need more control. In that case choose the
appropriate search engine in the "Detailed search's" section and click on it
to go to that section. Then enter you're search parameters and go.

3) You're not sure what you are looking for or just want to browse. Click on
the "or try Tachyon's personal hotlist" link to look through my own collection
of sites.
@endnode

@node "History" "History"
@next "Bugs"
@prev "Instructions"
History:

3.0 - total rewrite of the entire TachySearch code. New search engines added,
new logo, added tables for neatness and to make better use of space for those
with smaller browser screens. Also should now be compatible with browsers
other than IBrowse. Even works with (yuk) NetScape.

2.1a - same as 2.1 but with a minor bug fix due to an editor macro error.

2.1 - first actual public release, added a few things, fixed the logo graphics
and a few bugs

2.0 and under - My own use versions which pretty much sucked.
@endnode

